  1050→## Tips
  1052→### Sending form data
  1054→Sending form data in Ky is identical to `fetch`. Just pass a [`FormData`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/FormData) instance to the `body` option. The `Content-Type` header will be automatically set to `multipart/form-data`, overriding any existing `Content-Type` header.
  1055→
      →…
  1158→#### Native proxy support
  1160→Node.js 24.5+ supports automatic proxy configuration via environment variables. Set `NODE_USE_ENV_PROXY=1` or use the `--use-env-proxy` CLI flag.
  1161→
  1162→```sh
  1163→NODE_USE_ENV_PROXY=1 HTTP_PROXY=http://proxy.example.com:8080 node app.js
  1164→```
  1165→
  1166→Or:
  1167→
  1168→```sh
  1169→node --use-env-proxy app.js
  1170→```
  1171→
